  "text": "HomeCareersWe'll discuss her career transition from beauty reporter to fragrance brand founder, how she built the business into a Sephora success story, Ellis Brooklyn's 10th anniversary and more.Steph here. I'm so excited to share that I'll be joined by Ellis Brooklyn Founder and CEO Bee Shapiro on The Fashionista Network. But here's the best part: I want you to join me! It's your opportunity to interact live with us, ask questions and be a part of the show.In addition to her fragrance business, Shapiro is also a longtime New York Times beauty columnist as well as the author of \"Skin Deep: Women on Skin Care, Makeup, and Looking Their Best,\" a compilation of her best-read columns.She founded Ellis Brooklyn in 2015, and has since grown it to include body care as well as luxury, \"clean\" fragrances, partnering with retailers including Sephora, Ulta and Revolve. In 2023, the company closed a seed round of funding, led by Stage 1 Financials' Stage 1 Fund, which includes Nyx founder Toni Ko.Â We'll discuss all of this and more in our live show.Scroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesThis conversation will be publicly accessible (no paywall!) on The Fashionista Network, powered by interactive media platform Fireside, and you'll get the chance to participate and join the stage with video to ask questions directly. Learn more about The Fashionista Network here.You don't want to miss this show on Thursday, June 26 at 1:00 p.m. ET / 10:00 a.m. PT. Sign up for free access now (and don't forget to become a member to access all of our members-only shows and perks as well).From emerging startups to Fortune 500 companies, brands are building awareness, driving sales and gaining followers by partnering with Fashionista. Discover our unique digital offerings here.Homepage photo: Courtesy of Ellis BrooklynSubscribe to Our Newsletter",
